'''''Bothriochloa macra''''', commonly known as known as '''red-leg grass''',<ref name=NSW/>  '''red grass''',<ref name=NSW>{{NSW Flora Online|author= |genus=Bothriochloa |species=macra }}</ref> '''redleg'''<ref Name=GRIN/> or '''pitted beard grass'''<ref name=GRIN/> is a perennial grass species that is native to [[eastern Australia]] and [[New Zealand]].<ref name=GRIN>{{GRIN | name =''Bothriochloa macra'' | id = 412214| accessdate = 4 May 2014}}</ref> It is naturalised in [[Tasmania]] and [[Norfolk Island]].<ref name=APNI>{{APNI| name =''Bothriochloa macra'' | id =8575 | accessdate = 5 May 2014 }}</ref>

